latestPosts.caption:
Celebrate the 4th of July with this Piña Colada refresher that is red, white and BEET-iful!❤️💙💕 

Recipe:

Blue: 
1 cup almond milk, unsweetened
1.5 cups frozen pineapple
1 banana, frozen
¼ ripe avocado
½ cup crushed ice
½ tsp vanilla
¼ tsp blue spirulina
¾ cup coconut yogurt 

Red:
1 cup frozen strawberries
1 tbsp maple syrup or honey
2 Love Beets Organic Cooked Beets
Juice of ½ a lime
½ cup crushed ice 

Directions
Add the “Blue” ingredients and ¼ cup of the coconut yogurt into a high powered blender. Blend until smooth. Divide the remaining ½ cup of coconut yogurt between 2 large glasses, spreading across the bottom and up the sides of the glass. Sprinkle additional Blue Spirulina along the sides of the glass, allowing it to mix with the yogurt. Pour half of the Blue smoothie into one glass, the rest into another. In the same blender, add the “Red” ingredients, blending until smooth. Add a small amount of water to aid blending if necessary. Splitting between 2 glasses, pour the Red refresher over top of the Blue smoothie. Add a straw or spoon and enjoy!

#lovebeets #cooked #beets #refresher #4thofjuly

Making our Monday BEET-er with this dreamy strawberry and beet smoothie.☁️🍓💕

RECIPE:

1 cup frozen strawberries
1-2 Organic Cooked Beets
1/2 frozen banana or 1 small banana
1/2 cup Greek yogurt
1/2 cup coconut yogurt
1 tsp vanilla extract

Blend ingredients in a blender until completely smooth. Add some yogurt into your glass with a spoon and fill the glass with the smoothie. Enjoy!

#lovebeets #cookedbeets #beetsmoothie

Each bite of this Chickpea & Beet Sandwich just get BEET=er and better.😉🥪💕

RECIPE:

6 slices of Love Beets Perfectly Pickled Beets 
Arugula or Pea Shoots, for serving 
4 slices of Sourdough Bread, toasted, for serving 

For the Smashed Chickpea Salad: 
1 15-oz can Chickpeas, drained and rinsed 
1/3 cup Walnuts, or Pecans, roasted and chopped 
1/4 cup Plain Greek Yogurt 
1 Celery Stalk, finely chopped 
2 tbsp. Carrots, finely chopped (optional) 
2 tsp. Dijon Mustard 
1/2 Lemon, juiced 
2 tbsp. Fresh Parsley, chopped 
1 tbsp. Apple Cider Vinegar 
1/4 tsp. Salt 
1/2 tsp. Black Pepper 

Add the chickpeas into a large bowl, then use a potato masher or fork to smash at least half of the chickpeas. Add in the chopped nuts, fresh parsley, celery, and (optional) carrots, then toss until well combined. In a separate bowl, whisk together the lemon juice, apple cider vinegar, Dijon mustard, plain Greek yogurt, salt, and black pepper. Add the yogurt mixture into the smashed chickpeas, then give it one last toss to combine. Add half of the smashed chickpea salad onto one slice of toasted sourdough bread, then add three sliced pickled beets, and a small handful pea shoots. Top with another slice of toasted bread, then enjoy!

#lovebeets #beets #readytoeat #chickpea #sandwich
